= Main Findings

This chapter synthesises the findings from all experimental chapters into a cohesive narrative. Rather than repeating results, it should draw out the overarching themes, patterns, and contributions that emerge when the individual studies are considered together.

== [Topic or Research Question 1]

Synthesise the findings relevant to your first major research question or theme across all experimental chapters. Discuss how the evidence from different studies converges or diverges.

== [Topic or Research Question 2]

Synthesise the findings relevant to your second research question or theme. Draw connections between the individual study results.

== [Additional Topics as Needed]

Continue for each major research question or theme.

== Summary

Provide a concise summary of the main findings of the thesis as a whole, drawing together the threads from the sections above. This should give the reader a clear picture of what the thesis has found before moving to a discussion of wider implications.
